A 4-year-old male is brought to your office by his mother because of fevers, irritability, runny
nose, and cough for the past week. On examination he is noted to have bilateral conjunctivitis;
dry cracked lips; a maculopapular rash; edema and erythema of his palms and soles bilaterally;
and a nontender, enlarged, right anterior cervical lymph node.
Which one of the following should be included in the evaluation of this patient’s condition?
